<br>
Carefully she stands, gently cradling the bottle in her large hands, and makes her way back to the kitchen. From a linen cupboard she takes a soft velvet cloth and places it on the small table near the old cookbook. Reverently, she places the bottle on the cloth covered table.<br>
<br>
"It be time, Old Spirits. This be th time ye've been waitin fer. I call upon yer ancient providence ta bless this workin which we are about ta undertake an ask that yer power infuse an bless all that partake of ye." Mirabor finishes reciting her prayer and turns to the cookbook, turning the pages to the older recipes in the back, looking with fondness at the archaic writing as the pages turn under her careful fingers.<br>
<br>
"Ah, here it is... <I>'A Craefted Wydding Cayke to Warde Agaenst Evil'</I>... that's what be needed here." Mira carefully memorizes the ingredients stopping at the line for 'Thyrtein drams of Purehyrt Brandye.' She smiles and looks at the bottle on the small table. "Long has it been since ya blessed a union. Pureheart Brandy are ya? Aye, that be fittin indeed."<br>
<br>
She carefully opens the bottle and measures the exact amount with a special alchemy vial, then carries the bottle back to its resting place in the cellar alcove. Returning to the kitchen, she gets out her ingredients and sets to work.<br>
<br>
<br>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=230 HEIGHT=154 SRC="http://www.foxgrovecircle.org/eq/evcake.jpg">Some time later, Mira emerges from the kitchen with a simple cake and places it on the table. "Congratulations on yer engagement, dear Eviah! Come, Sisters! Gather th lads! Come an let's celebrate yer betrothal with this cake which I've made special just fer you."<br>
<br>
Fetching the special crystal goblets from the Gnomish Murphy Bar, she pours some sparkling cider from the decanter and raises a toast. "To yer future! May ye always find happiness t'gether."<br>
